race.comment: TERRITORY MAN (6) followed a solid third when fresh from a spell at Belmont with a win as the favourite over 1400m here two weeks ago, scoring by nearly a length. There is more depth to this field, but William Pike sticks with him, and so do we. SUPER ROMANI (1) was out of the money, but not far away when resuming over 1400m at this track last start. He usually improves with racing, and with a drop in class, with the aid of a 3kg claim, he can figure in the top three this time. BLACK FOR CASH (5) ran fourth, just over a length away over 1400m here two weeks ago, and steps up to a more suitable trip this time. He will be running on strongly, and can have the last say here. MY HARV (9) resumed over 1500m here last start, sitting on the pace before kicking clear to win by half a length. There is more depth to this field, but she is stronger this season and can be competitive again. CLASSIC IMPACT (10) will find this easier than her last couple of starts, so don't risk her at decent odds.
